fields.title: Debt Item 1
fields.description: As a(n) developer of Forem (Office wallon de la formation professionnelle et de l’emploi), I find that it is increasingly risky to deploy in the ACC/FORM/PROD environments because we rely on the infrastructure team, and the tools in place do not enable us to react quickly and independently in case of a deployment failure.

fields.title: Debt Item 2
fields.description: As a(n) developer of a development team, I find that it is increasingly frustrating to work with a common project template because the various supported cases add a lot of conditions to the code, and the main method has a high cyclomatic complexity.

fields.title: Debt Item 3
fields.description: As a(n) developer of a development team, I find that it is increasingly difficult to keep unit tests up to date because the existing tests are tightly coupled with the code structure, making code refactoring impossible.

fields.title: Debt Item 4
fields.description: As a(n) back-end developer of a development team, I find that it is increasingly risky to deploy a new version because we don't have feedback on whether the integration is working.

fields.title: Debt Item 5
fields.description: As a(n) developer of a development team, I find that it is increasingly frustrating to debug/refactor because some architectural/technical decisions have been changed multiple times.

fields.title: Debt Item 6
fields.description: As a(n) developer of a development team, I find that it is increasingly time-consuming to perform end-to-end tests because the features are becoming more numerous, and sometimes, minor modifications lead to breaking changes.

fields.title: Debt Item 7
fields.description: As a(n) developer of a development team, I find that it is increasingly frustrating to refer to the internal documentation because it's not always up-to-date.

fields.title: Debt Item 8
fields.description: As a(n) analyst and user of Azure DevOps, I find that it is increasingly time-consuming to copy user stories into Azure DevOps from the requirements document because it's copy-pasting.

fields.title: Debt Item 9
fields.description: As a(n) user of Azure DevOps, I find that it is increasingly difficult to make sense of things in the projects because the structure is not user-friendly.

fields.title: Debt Item 10
fields.description: As a(n) developer of project collaboration spaces, I find that it is increasingly risky to not centralize the flow of requests addressed to the team because information can get lost, backups may not exist and the service's continuity could be interrupted.

fields.title: Debt Item 11
fields.description: As a(n) developer of project collaboration spaces, I find that it is increasingly frustrating to address business issues within these applications because , at times, the resolution is urgent, the problem is complex, and the documentation is weak or even nonexistent.

fields.title: Debt Item 12
fields.description: As a(n) security expert of the Application Security Team, I find that it is increasingly difficult to manage the risks posed by open-source components because there is a lack of visibility and validation.

fields.title: Debt Item 13
fields.description: As a(n) security expert of the Application Security team, I find that it is increasingly risky to not conduct application penetration tests because the lack of penetration tests limits visibility on security risks/vulnerabilities.

fields.title: Debt Item 14
fields.description: As a(n) security expert of the Application Security team, I find that it is increasingly risky to not conduct application penetration tests because it limits visibility on security vulnerabilities that are (easily) exploitable.

fields.title: Debt Item 15
fields.description: As a(n) security expert of the Application Security team, I find that it is increasingly time-consuming to compile reports on the quality/security of applications because the reports have to be compiled manually since there is no integrated dashboarding solution.

fields.title: Debt Item 16
fields.description: As a(n) developer of the Dev Support front-end team, I find that it is increasingly difficult to stay focused and make swift progress on certain development tasks because I'm interrupted multiple times for various requests from the developers.

fields.title: Debt Item 17
fields.description: As a(n) developer of the Dev Support front-end team, I find that it is increasingly difficult to be aware of certain needs from the development teams because , at times, they don't report the issues they encounter and find workarounds to achieve their goals, sometimes deviating from the standards.

fields.title: Debt Item 18
fields.description: As a(n) developer of the Dev Support front-end team, I find that it is increasingly difficult to ensure that the standards are well understood by the teams because there are very few developers who provide feedback, even during dedicated discussions.

fields.title: Debt Item 19
fields.description: As a(n) developer of the Dev Support front-end team, I find that it is increasingly time-consuming to wait for team members to be available to analyze the pull requests because they also have other tasks/aren't able to dedicate time to it.

fields.title: Debt Item 20
fields.description: As a(n) developer of the Dev Support front-end team, I find that it is increasingly risky to have to deploy components quickly in order to meet urgent demands because we don't have enough time to conduct sufficient tests.

fields.title: Debt Item 21
fields.description: As a(n) developer of the Dev Support front-end team, I find that it is increasingly time-consuming to implement all the tests on web components because they haven't been implemented in the past due to pressing requests or other reasons.

fields.title: Debt Item 22
fields.description: As a(n) member of the Dev Support team, I find that it is increasingly difficult to access up-to-date documentation because adding new documentation can conflict with existing documentation that we're unaware of, and the Azure DevOps tool is not intuitive and not structured enough to have accurate documentation.

fields.title: Debt Item 23
fields.description: As a(n) front-end developer of the Dev Support team, I find that it is increasingly risky to not  be able to closely track the various developments of the teams because we  do not have the necessary time/resources to monitor them.

fields.title: Debt Item 24
fields.description: As a(n) developer of the Dev Support team, I find that it is increasingly frustrating to adapt components to meet accessibility standards because the concerned guidelines evolve regularly as the individuals in charge of them are still in training.

fields.title: Debt Item 25
fields.description: As a(n) MOD developer of the Dev Support team, I find that it is increasingly risky to develop within shared components because we have limited feedback from developers on how they use them.

fields.title: Debt Item 26
fields.description: As a(n) MOD developer of the Dev Support team, I find that it is increasingly time-consuming to ensure that teams are using our shared components because we don't have a clear view of the usage.

fields.title: Debt Item 27
fields.description: As a(n) MOD developer of the Dev Support team, I find that it is increasingly risky to update the CI/CD pipelines because we don't have quick feedback on our errors.

fields.title: Debt Item 28
fields.description: As a(n) MOD developer of the Dev Support team, I find that it is increasingly time-consuming to know the rules that teams use in Azure DevOps because we don't have a clear view of the usage.

fields.title: Debt Item 29
fields.description: As a(n) MOD developer of the Dev Support team, I find that it is increasingly difficult to propose architectural solutions because our deployment model doesn't accommodate different use cases.

fields.title: Debt Item 30
fields.description: As a(n) MOD developer of the Dev Support team, I find that it is increasingly costly to update our guidelines because Microsoft is making significant changes to their APIs.

fields.title: Debt Item 31
fields.description: As a(n) MOD developer of the Dev Support team, I find that it is increasingly difficult to provide relevant answers to questions from developers because the developers don't provide us with sufficient context for their issues, and I can't easily run their application to observe the application's behavior.

fields.title: Debt Item 32
fields.description: As a(n) MOD developer of the Dev Support team, I find that it is increasingly difficult to motivate developers to add features to the shared components because they don't have time to collaborate and advocate for their code.

fields.title: Debt Item 33
fields.description: As a(n) MOD developer of the Dev Support team, I find that it is increasingly frustrating to engage in remote pair programming because I can't physically point or use a pointer on the other person's screen to highlight the part of the code I want to provide feedback on.

fields.title: Debt Item 34
fields.description: As a(n) analyst of the Development Department, I find that it is increasingly difficult to request a mock-up (and receive it on time) from the Digital Channels team because this team is understaffed.

fields.title: Debt Item 35
fields.description: As a(n) front-end developer of the Development Methodologies and Tools team, I find that it is increasingly frustrating to detect new Web Components features in the mock-ups of the Digital Channels team because the functionality does not exist.

fields.title: Debt Item 36
fields.description: As a(n) front-end developer of the Development Methodologies and Tools team, I find that it is increasingly risky to update a shared component quickly because the unit tests are not present or complete.

fields.title: Debt Item 37
fields.description: As a(n) front-end developer of the Front/UI team, I find that it is increasingly risky to modiy front-end components because the unit tests were not created on time.

fields.title: Debt Item 38
fields.description: As a(n) back-end developer of the GTS application, I find that it is increasingly difficult to understand the technical needs during the migration of certain components to .NET Core (e.g., those related to Hangfire) because it forced us to rethink the architecture of the application.

fields.title: Debt Item 39
fields.description: As a(n) application manager of the Helsinki team, I find that it is increasingly time-consuming to deploy in an environment because the process is very structured.

fields.title: Debt Item 40
fields.description: As a(n) analyst of the IT Department, I find that it is increasingly dangerous to deal with sensitive data and use it in applications because there is a lack of training on the use and securing of sensitive data.

fields.title: Debt Item 41
fields.description: As a(n) developer of the IT Department, I find that it is increasingly time-consuming to debug because there are too many dependencies.

fields.title: Debt Item 42
fields.description: As a(n) developer of the IT Department, I find that it is increasingly time-consuming to perform end-to-end tests of the application because the test cases are increasing over time, and we lack specialized profiles.

fields.title: Debt Item 43
fields.description: As a(n) developer of the IT Department, I find that it is increasingly difficult to maintain legacy scripts/programs because the only person who knew them has retired, and no one is motivated to learn the languages used.

fields.title: Debt Item 44
fields.description: As a(n) member of the IT Department, I find that it is increasingly frustrating to have to manage multiple sources of data because there are non-centralized pieces of information.

fields.title: Debt Item 45
fields.description: As a(n) member of the IT Department, I find that it is increasingly frustrating to have to deploy hotfixes for the IAR application on a regular basis because this disrupts the organization of days when application deployments are not normally planned.

fields.title: Debt Item 46
fields.description: As a(n) member of the IT Department, I find that it is increasingly frustrating to have to work with multiple tools (Azure DevOps, Jira, EasyVista) because I have to regularly input the same information in multiple places.

fields.title: Debt Item 47
fields.description: As a(n) MOD developer of the MOD team, I find that it is increasingly risky to maintain security-related components because I don't have a clear vision of the applications that call upon these libraries.

fields.title: Debt Item 48
fields.description: As a(n) member of the MOD team, I find that it is increasingly time-consuming to make technical or methodological changes because the number of teams is significant (communication issues, tracking, etc.).

fields.title: Debt Item 49
fields.description: As a(n) MOD developer of the MOD team, I find that it is increasingly risky to address technical debt within the components because the actual integration tests are conducted within the applications, and it's difficult/impossible to cover cases of which we aren't aware of.

fields.title: Debt Item 50
fields.description: As a(n) front-end developer of the Oslo team, I find that it is increasingly difficult to stay up to date with UI/UX standards because the use of the React framework does not allow the integration of Web Components.

fields.title: Debt Item 51
fields.description: As a(n) front-end developer of the Oslo team, I find that it is increasingly time-consuming to follow the organization's graphic charter because the technologies used do not allow for easy integration of standards.

fields.title: Debt Item 52
fields.description: As a(n) lead developer of the Rio team, I find that it is increasingly time-consuming to request a task to be performed by cross-functional teams because too many procedures put in place by teams, which hampers velocity.

fields.title: Debt Item 53
fields.description: As a(n) member of the Software Development Subdepartment, I find that it is increasingly frustrating to not have a user-centered approach from the start because this leads to negative feedback about the end users' experience with the applications.

fields.title: Debt Item 54
fields.description: As a(n) director of the Software Development Subdepartment, I find that it is increasingly risky to not  have an integration environment because it becomes impossible to test the applications before moving to Acceptance.

fields.title: Debt Item 55
fields.description: As a(n) director of the Software Development Subdepartment, I find that it is increasingly time-consuming to deploy APIs because the  work can only be done by a single team, creating a bottleneck.

fields.title: Debt Item 56
fields.description: As a(n) director of the Software Development Subdepartment, I find that it is increasingly difficult to to interact with the "citizens" data repository because key sorting or filtering functionalities are not performing well.

fields.title: Debt Item 57
fields.description: As a(n) director of the Software Development sub-department, I find that it is increasingly time-consuming to extract useful data from Jira because I'm forced to perform exports to Excel for further manipulations.

fields.title: Debt Item 58
fields.description: As a(n) web designer of the UI/UX team, I find that it is increasingly difficult to clearly keep track of all the decisions made during meetings and follow their developments because we do not have a shared dashboard / tracking tool.
